Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.28,0:03:03.30,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8\pos(192,152)}{\fn方正兰亭中黑_GBK\fs30\b0\bord0\shad0\3c&H2F2F2F&\c&HFFFFFF&}面  试
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.18,0:03:14.78,Default,,0,0,0,,你好  我和乌尔曼先生有预约\N{\rEng}Hi. I've got an appointment with Mr. Ullman.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.78,0:03:16.75,Default,,0,0,0,,我叫杰克·托伦斯\N{\rEng}My name is Jack Torrance.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.89,0:03:19.28,Default,,0,0,0,,他的办公室是左手边第一间\N{\rEng}His office is the first door on the left.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.67,0:03:20.74,Default,,0,0,0,,谢谢\N{\rEng}Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.25,0:03:39.20,Default,,0,0,0,,-乌尔曼先生  -正是\N{\rEng}- Mr. Ullman? - Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.20,0:03:42.90,Default,,0,0,0,,-我是杰克·托伦斯  -快请进  杰克\N{\rEng}- I'm Jack Torrance. - Oh, come on in, Jack.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.87,0:03:45.03,Default,,0,0,0,,很高兴认识你\N{\rEng}Very nice to meet you.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.03,0:03:46.53,Default,,0,0,0,,我也很高兴认识你  乌尔曼先生\N{\rEng}Nice to meet you too, Mr. Ullman.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.53,0:03:48.46,Default,,0,0,0,,-这是我的秘书  苏希  -你好\N{\rEng}- This is my secretary, Susie. - Hello.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.46,0:03:51.19,Default,,0,0,0,,-苏希  你好  -我们这里难找吗\N{\rEng}- Susie, how do you do? - Any trouble finding us?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.19,0:03:54.50,Default,,0,0,0,,一点不难找  我三个半小时就到了\N{\rEng}No problem at all. I made the trip in 3 and a half hours.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.50,0:03:56.05,Default,,0,0,0,,那真是算很快了\N{\rEng}That's very good time.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.05,0:03:58.18,Default,,0,0,0,,快请坐吧  杰克\N{\rEng}Sit down a minute, Jack.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.18,0:04:00.12,Default,,0,0,0,,在这千万别拘束\N{\rEng}Just make yourself at home.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.25,0:04:01.65,Default,,0,0,0,,要来杯咖啡吗\N{\rEng}Would you like some coffee?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.75,0:04:04.43,Default,,0,0,0,,如果有的话  就来点吧  谢谢\N{\rEng}If you're having some, I wouldn't mind. Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.43,0:04:05.62,Default,,0,0,0,,-苏希  -好\N{\rEng}- Susie. - Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.62,0:04:07.59,Default,,0,0,0,,去叫比尔·沃森来跟我们一起\N{\rEng}And would you ask Bill Watson to join us.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.59,0:04:09.33,Default,,0,0,0,,好的  我这就去\N{\rEng}Yes, I will.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.87,0:04:20.93,Default,,0,0,0,,妈妈\N{\rEng}Mom?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.91,0:04:23.02,Default,,0,0,0,,怎么了\N{\rEng}Yeah?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.47,0:04:26.62,Default,,0,0,0,,你真的想去住在那个酒店里过冬天吗\N{\rEng}Do you really want to go and live in that hotel for the winter?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.65,0:04:28.77,Default,,0,0,0,,当然了\N{\rEng}Sure I do.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.32,0:04:30.83,Default,,0,0,0,,肯定很好玩\N{\rEng}It'll be lots of fun.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.04,0:04:34.95,Default,,0,0,0,,好吧  应该是吧\N{\rEng}Yeah. I guess so.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.41,0:04:39.00,Default,,0,0,0,,反正  这里也没什么人一起玩\N{\rEng}Anyway, there's hardly anybody to play with around here.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.70,0:04:44.72,Default,,0,0,0,,我知道  结交新朋友总是需要花些时间的\N{\rEng}I know. It always takes a little time to make new friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.46,0:04:47.38,Default,,0,0,0,,是啊  或许是吧\N{\rEng}Yeah, I guess so.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.52,0:04:49.73,Default,,0,0,0,,托尼呢\N{\rEng}What about Tony?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.77,0:04:51.85,Default,,0,0,0,,我猜他肯定很期待去酒店\N{\rEng}He's looking forward to the hotel, I bet.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.72,0:04:54.75,Default,,0,0,0,,不  我才不呢  托伦斯夫人\N{\rEng}No, I ain't, Mrs. Torrance.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.46,0:04:57.64,Default,,0,0,0,,拜托  托尼  别犯傻了\N{\rEng}Now, come on, Tony. Don't be silly.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.27,0:05:00.45,Default,,0,0,0,,我不想去那里  托伦斯夫人\N{\rEng}I don't want to go there, Mrs. Torrance.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.94,0:05:02.39,Default,,0,0,0,,你为什么不想去呢\N{\rEng}How come you don't want to go?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.97,0:05:04.85,Default,,0,0,0,,我就是不想去\N{\rEng}I just don't.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.35,0:05:07.67,Default,,0,0,0,,那我们就走着瞧吧\N{\rEng}Let's just wait and see.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.40,0:05:10.82,Default,,0,0,0,,我们都会玩得很开心的\N{\rEng}We're all going to have a real good time.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.45,0:05:15.13,Default,,0,0,0,,比尔  我想介绍你认识一下杰克·托伦斯\N{\rEng}Bill, I'd like you to meet Jack Torrance.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.13,0:05:16.68,Default,,0,0,0,,-你好  比尔  -你好\N{\rEng}- How do you do, Bill? - How do you do.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.68,0:05:18.80,Default,,0,0,0,,-很高兴认识你  -很高兴认识你\N{\rEng}- Nice to meet you. - Pleasure to meet you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.94,0:05:20.69,Default,,0,0,0,,坐吧  比尔  一起聊聊\N{\rEng}Grab a chair, Bill. Join in.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.01,0:05:24.83,Default,,0,0,0,,杰克今年冬天会帮我们照看眺望酒店\N{\rEng}Jack is going to take care of the Overlook for us this winter.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.43,0:05:28.34,Default,,0,0,0,,等我们谈完  希望你带他四处转转\N{\rEng}I'd like you to take him around place soon as we're through.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.34,0:05:29.44,Default,,0,0,0,,好的\N{\rEng}Fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.14,0:05:31.82,Default,,0,0,0,,杰克是学校里的老师\N{\rEng}Jack is a schoolteacher.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.33,0:05:34.21,Default,,0,0,0,,以前是老师\N{\rEng}Uh, formerly a schoolteacher.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.51,0:05:36.07,Default,,0,0,0,,你现在做什么工作\N{\rEng}What line of work are you in now?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.38,0:05:37.62,Default,,0,0,0,,我是个作家\N{\rEng}I'm a writer.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.21,0:05:41.95,Default,,0,0,0,,教书差不多就是为了糊口而已\N{\rEng}Teaching's been more or less a way of making ends meet.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.95,0:05:43.97,Default,,0,0,0,,如今这样对你来说应该是个很大的变化\N{\rEng}This ought to be quite a change for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.22,0:05:46.94,Default,,0,0,0,,我很期待有变化\N{\rEng}Well, I'm looking for a change.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.99,0:05:49.69,Default,,0,0,0,,我们在丹佛的人强烈推荐杰克\N{\rEng}Our people in Denver recommended Jack very highly,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.69,0:05:50.92,Default,,0,0,0,,这一次\N{\rEng}and for once...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.94,0:05:52.18,Default,,0,0,0,,我同意他们说的\N{\rEng}I agree with them.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.02,0:05:54.21,Default,,0,0,0,,刚刚说到哪了\N{\rEng}Let's see, where were we?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.21,0:05:56.28,Default,,0,0,0,,我刚刚  准备给你解释\N{\rEng}I was ,yeah, about to explain...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.28,0:06:02.26,Default,,0,0,0,,我们的营业季是从5月15号到10月30号\N{\rEng}that our season here runs from may 15th to October 30th.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.26,0:06:05.61,Default,,0,0,0,,然后彻底停业  到第二年的5月再开业\N{\rEng}Then we close down completely until the following May.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.87,0:06:08.53,Default,,0,0,0,,我能问问为什么吗\N{\rEng}Do you mind if I ask why you do that?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.93,0:06:12.60,Default,,0,0,0,,在我看来在这里滑雪应该会很棒\N{\rEng}It seems to me that the skiing up here would be fantastic.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.60,0:06:15.16,Default,,0,0,0,,的确是的  问题在于要花费巨大的成本\N{\rEng}It would be. The problem is the enormous cost...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.16,0:06:17.16,Default,,0,0,0,,维持到萨德温德镇的路面能够通行\N{\rEng}it would be to keep the road to Sidewinder open.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.16,0:06:20.51,Default,,0,0,0,,那是段25英里的路\N{\rEng}It's a 25-mile stretch of road.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.51,0:06:23.12,Default,,0,0,0,,冬天的降雪厚度能有20英尺\N{\rEng}It gets 20 feet of snow during the winter.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.12,0:06:28.19,Default,,0,0,0,,要保持路面畅通  从经济上来看是完全不划算的\N{\rEng}There's just no way to make it economically feasible to keep it clear.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.75,0:06:31.23,Default,,0,0,0,,1907年建这个地方的时候\N{\rEng}When the place was built in 1907...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.23,0:06:34.02,Default,,0,0,0,,人们对冬季运动尚不感兴趣\N{\rEng}there was very little interest in winter sports.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.02,0:06:38.81,Default,,0,0,0,,选择这里完全是看中其幽静的环境和美丽的风景\N{\rEng}This site was chosen for its seclusion and scenic beauty.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.09,0:06:41.57,Default,,0,0,0,,这里的确够幽静和美丽的\N{\rEng}It's certainly got plenty of that.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.75,0:06:42.99,Default,,0,0,0,,没错\N{\rEng}That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.04,0:06:46.21,Default,,0,0,0,,在丹佛时  他们有没有告诉你\N{\rEng}Did they give you any idea in Denver...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.21,0:06:48.51,Default,,0,0,0,,这份工作具体是做什么的\N{\rEng}about what the job entails?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.66,0:06:50.63,Default,,0,0,0,,就大致说了一下\N{\rEng}Only in a very general way.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.30,0:06:56.20,Default,,0,0,0,,冬季真的会无比残酷\N{\rEng}The winters can be fantastically cruel.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.20,0:07:00.01,Default,,0,0,0,,基本就是要应对高额的损坏\N{\rEng}The basic idea is to cope with the very costly damage...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.01,0:07:02.00,Default,,0,0,0,,以及可能出现的折旧\N{\rEng}and depreciation which can occur.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.00,0:07:04.55,Default,,0,0,0,,这主要包括烧锅炉\N{\rEng}This consists mainly of running the boiler...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.55,0:07:08.51,Default,,0,0,0,,每天例行给酒店的不同区域供暖\N{\rEng}heating different parts of the hotel on a daily rotating basis...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.74,0:07:10.76,Default,,0,0,0,,出现损坏及时修理\N{\rEng}repairing damage as it occurs...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.76,0:07:14.08,Default,,0,0,0,,及时修理小毛病就不会变成大问题\N{\rEng}and doing repairs so the elements can't get a foothold.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.53,0:07:17.36,Default,,0,0,0,,我觉得没有问题\N{\rEng}That sounds fine to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.12,0:07:21.02,Default,,0,0,0,,从体力上说  这份工作要求不高\N{\rEng}Physically, it's not a very demanding job.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.23,0:07:22.44,Default,,0,0,0,,在冬天  唯一一件\N{\rEng}The only thing that can
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.44,0:07:24.11,Default,,0,0,0,,可能会有点难熬的事情\N{\rEng}get a bit trying here during the winter...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.11,0:07:27.20,Default,,0,0,0,,就是会有强烈的孤独感\N{\rEng}is a tremendous sense of isolation.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.40,0:07:32.36,Default,,0,0,0,,那恰恰就是我想寻求的\N{\rEng}Well, that just happens to be exactly what I'm looking for.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.36,0:07:35.75,Default,,0,0,0,,我正在写新作品的大纲\N{\rEng}I'm outlining a new writing project.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.75,0:07:39.99,Default,,0,0,0,,五个月宁静的时光正是我想要的\N{\rEng}And, five months of peace is just what I want.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.95,0:07:42.43,Default,,0,0,0,,那很好  杰克\N{\rEng}That's very good, Jack.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.99,0:07:46.00,Default,,0,0,0,,因为  对有的人来说\N{\rEng}Because, for some people...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.50,0:07:49.64,Default,,0,0,0,,孤独  与世隔绝\N{\rEng}solitude ...and isolation...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.06,0:07:52.87,Default,,0,0,0,,本身  就会成为问题\N{\rEng}can, of itself, become a problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.88,0:07:55.16,Default,,0,0,0,,我不会\N{\rEng}Not for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.05,0:07:57.29,Default,,0,0,0,,你夫人和儿子呢\N{\rEng}How about your wife and son?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.29,0:07:59.03,Default,,0,0,0,,你觉得他们能接受吗\N{\rEng}Do you think they'll take to it?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.08,0:08:02.41,Default,,0,0,0,,他们会很喜欢的\N{\rEng}They'll love it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.53,0:08:03.66,Default,,0,0,0,,好极了\N{\rEng}Great.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.02,0:08:09.50,Default,,0,0,0,,在我把你交接给比尔之前\N{\rEng}Well, before I turn you over to Bill,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.01,0:08:13.74,Default,,0,0,0,,我觉得还有一件事我们需要聊聊\N{\rEng}there's one other thing I think we should talk about.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.74,0:08:15.36,Default,,0,0,0,,我也不想耸人听闻\N{\rEng}I don't want to sound melodramatic,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.36,0:08:18.13,Default,,0,0,0,,但是这件事的确会让有些人\N{\rEng}but it's something been known to give a few people
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.13,0:08:20.00,Default,,0,0,0,,犹豫到底要不要接受这份工作\N{\rEng}second thoughts about the job.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.05,0:08:22.57,Default,,0,0,0,,我很有兴趣知道\N{\rEng}I'm intrigued.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.87,0:08:25.41,Default,,0,0,0,,我觉得在丹佛时他们应该没告诉你\N{\rEng}I don't suppose they tell you anything in Denver
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.41,0:08:29.25,Default,,0,0,0,,1970年冬天发生在这里的一起悲剧事件\N{\rEng}about the tragedy we had up here during the winter of 1970.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.13,0:08:31.83,Default,,0,0,0,,他们似乎的确没说\N{\rEng}I don't believe they did.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.26,0:08:37.11,Default,,0,0,0,,我这个职位的前任负责人\N{\rEng}My predecessor in this job
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.11,0:08:40.46,Default,,0,0,0,,雇了一个叫查尔斯·格拉迪的人当冬季管理员\N{\rEng}hired a man named Charles Grady as the winter caretaker.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.46,0:08:42.69,Default,,0,0,0,,他是带着夫人和两个女儿一起来的\N{\rEng}He came up with his wife and two little girls
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.69,0:08:44.10,Default,,0,0,0,,一个8岁  一个10岁\N{\rEng}of about 8 and 10.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.19,0:08:46.27,Default,,0,0,0,,他过去的工作记录很好\N{\rEng}He had a good employment record,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.44,0:08:47.56,Default,,0,0,0,,推荐信都对他赞不绝口\N{\rEng}good references.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.56,0:08:48.64,Default,,0,0,0,,据我所知道的信息\N{\rEng}And from what I've been told,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.64,0:08:52.59,Default,,0,0,0,,他似乎是一个非常正常的人\N{\rEng}he seemed like a completely normal individual.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.73,0:08:55.24,Default,,0,0,0,,但是在冬天的某个时候\N{\rEng}But at some point during the winter
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.24,0:08:56.58,Default,,0,0,0,,他一定是经受了\N{\rEng}he must have suffered
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.58,0:08:59.26,Default,,0,0,0,,某种程度上的精神崩溃\N{\rEng}some kind of a complete mental breakdown.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.26,0:09:01.55,Default,,0,0,0,,他发狂了  然后...\N{\rEng}He ran amuck and...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.95,0:09:07.00,Default,,0,0,0,,用一把斧子杀了全家人\N{\rEng}killed his family with an ax.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.41,0:09:12.63,Default,,0,0,0,,把他们整齐地码在西翼的一个房间里  然后他...\N{\rEng}Stacked them neatly in a room in the west wing, and then he...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.59,0:09:17.31,Default,,0,0,0,,他把双管猎枪对准了嘴里  举枪自尽了\N{\rEng}he put both barrels of his shotgun in his mouth.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.68,0:09:20.16,Default,,0,0,0,,警方...\N{\rEng}The police...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.72,0:09:24.73,Default,,0,0,0,,警方认为这就是人们以前常说的幽闭症\N{\rEng}they thought that it was what the old-timers used to call cabin fever.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.01,0:09:27.92,Default,,0,0,0,,这种幽闭恐惧反应可能会出现在\N{\rEng}A kind of claustrophobic reaction which can occur
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.92,0:09:31.93,Default,,0,0,0,,一群人被困在一起很长时间之后\N{\rEng}when people are shut in together over long periods of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.41,0:09:38.57,Default,,0,0,0,,那还真是...\N{\rEng}That is...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.02,0:09:40.42,Default,,0,0,0,,相当离奇的故事\N{\rEng}quite a story.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.92,0:09:43.11,Default,,0,0,0,,是啊  的确\N{\rEng}Yeah, it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.48,0:09:47.47,Default,,0,0,0,,我还是很难相信这事真的是在这里发生的\N{\rEng}It's still hard for me to believe it actually happened here.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.02,0:09:49.80,Default,,0,0,0,,但事实如此\N{\rEng}But it did.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.03,0:09:51.26,Default,,0,0,0,,然后\N{\rEng}And, uh
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.57,0:09:55.23,Default,,0,0,0,,我觉得你应该能理解我为什么要告诉你\N{\rEng}I think you can appreciate why I wanted to tell you about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.72,0:09:58.26,Default,,0,0,0,,我当然理解\N{\rEng}I certainly can.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.08,0:10:01.86,Default,,0,0,0,,我也理解为什么你在丹佛的那些手下\N{\rEng}I also understand why your people in Denver
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.86,0:10:03.75,Default,,0,0,0,,把这事留给你来亲自告诉我\N{\rEng}left it for you to tell me.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.38,0:10:07.98,Default,,0,0,0,,显然  有些人一想到\N{\rEng}Obviously, some people can be put off
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.98,0:10:09.61,Default,,0,0,0,,要在发生过这种事的地方\N{\rEng}by the idea of staying alone in a place
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.65,0:10:12.37,Default,,0,0,0,,单独待这么久的时间  的确会打退堂鼓\N{\rEng}where something like that actually happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.60,0:10:15.19,Default,,0,0,0,,你大可安心  乌尔曼先生\N{\rEng}Well, you can rest assured Mr. Ullman,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.19,0:10:17.21,Default,,0,0,0,,我不会打退堂鼓的\N{\rEng}that's not going to happen with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.63,0:10:21.11,Default,,0,0,0,,至于我夫人那边\N{\rEng}And as far as my wife is concerned
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.56,0:10:25.16,Default,,0,0,0,,我相信等我告诉她  她会被深深地吸引住\N{\rEng}I'm sure she'll be absolutely fascinated when I tell her.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.16,0:10:30.81,Default,,0,0,0,,她是个忠实的鬼故事  恐怖电影爱好者\N{\rEng}She's a confirmed ghost story and horror film addict.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.93,0:10:39.31,Default,,0,0,0,,托尼  你觉得爸爸能拿到这份工作吗\N{\rEng}Tony, do you think dad'll get the job?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.02,0:10:42.79,Default,,0,0,0,,他已经拿到了\N{\rEng}He already did.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.60,0:10:47.04,Default,,0,0,0,,几分钟后他就要打给温蒂告诉她了\N{\rEng}He's going to phone Wendy up in a few minutes to tell her.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.72,0:11:01.80,Default,,0,0,0,,喂\N{\rEng}Hello.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.11,0:11:04.94,Default,,0,0,0,,-嗨  宝贝  -嗨  亲爱的  还顺利吗\N{\rEng}- Hi, babe. - Hi, hon. How's it going?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.94,0:11:07.10,Default,,0,0,0,,好极了  我还在酒店里\N{\rEng}Great. Look, I'm at the hotel
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.10,0:11:08.86,Default,,0,0,0,,接下来有一堆事情要去做\N{\rEng}and I still have a awful lot to go through.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.86,0:11:11.76,Default,,0,0,0,,我觉得我9点甚至10点前是到不了家了\N{\rEng}I don't think I can get home before 9:00 or 10:00.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.01,0:11:13.61,Default,,0,0,0,,听起来你已经得到这份工作了\N{\rEng}Sounds like you got the job.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.73,0:11:16.66,Default,,0,0,0,,没错  这地方很美\N{\rEng}Right. It's a beautiful place.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.66,0:11:18.62,Default,,0,0,0,,你和丹尼肯定会喜欢的\N{\rEng}You and Danny are going to love it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.32,0:11:22.88,Default,,0,0,0,,托尼  你为什么不想去那家酒店\N{\rEng}Tony, why don't you want to go to the hotel?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.49,0:11:24.67,Default,,0,0,0,,我不知道\N{\rEng}I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.21,0:11:29.39,Default,,0,0,0,,你肯定知道  快点告诉我\N{\rEng}You do too know. Now come on, tell me.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.52,0:11:31.92,Default,,0,0,0,,我不想说\N{\rEng}I don't want to.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.23,0:11:34.89,Default,,0,0,0,,拜托啦\N{\rEng}Please.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.65,0:11:36.85,Default,,0,0,0,,不\N{\rEng}No.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.19,0:11:38.85,Default,,0,0,0,,托尼  告诉我\N{\rEng}Now, Tony, tell me.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.07,0:12:11.47,Default,,0,0,0,,现在把眼睛睁开让我看看\N{\rEng}Now, hold your eyes still so I can see.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.40,0:12:18.19,Default,,0,0,0,,很好  另一只\N{\rEng}That's good. Now the other one.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.00,0:12:21.08,Default,,0,0,0,,好孩子\N{\rEng}Good boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.76,0:12:29.92,Default,,0,0,0,,丹尼\N{\rEng}Now, Danny
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.57,0:12:32.65,Default,,0,0,0,,你记不记得在刷牙的时候\N{\rEng}when you were brushing your teeth
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.80,0:12:36.01,Default,,0,0,0,,闻到什么奇怪的气味\N{\rEng}do you remember if you smelled anything funny
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.01,0:12:38.63,Default,,0,0,0,,或者看到什么强烈的闪光\N{\rEng}or saw any bright, flashing lights
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.63,0:12:41.01,Default,,0,0,0,,或是任何奇怪的东西\N{\rEng}or anything at all strange?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.58,0:12:44.65,Default,,0,0,0,,没有\N{\rEng}No.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.85,0:12:48.18,Default,,0,0,0,,你还记得你之前在刷牙吗\N{\rEng}Do you remember when you were brushing your teeth?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.95,0:12:50.14,Default,,0,0,0,,记得\N{\rEng}Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.35,0:12:54.73,Default,,0,0,0,,刷牙之后紧接着发生的事  你还记得什么\N{\rEng}What's the next thing you remember after you were brushing your teeth?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.29,0:13:02.89,Default,,0,0,0,,我妈妈在说  "醒醒  醒醒  丹尼  醒醒"\N{\rEng}My mom was saying, "Wake up. Wake up, Danny, wake up. "
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.09,0:13:08.31,Default,,0,0,0,,丹尼  你还记不记得\N{\rEng}Now, Danny, can you remember what you were doing
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.44,0:13:11.11,Default,,0,0,0,,在开始刷牙之前你在做什么\N{\rEng}just before you started brushing your teeth?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.92,0:13:15.30,Default,,0,0,0,,和托尼说话\N{\rEng}Talking to Tony.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.33,0:13:18.30,Default,,0,0,0,,托尼是你的宠物吗\N{\rEng}Is Tony one of your animals?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.58,0:13:22.24,Default,,0,0,0,,不  他是住在我嘴里的小男孩\N{\rEng}No. He's a little boy that lives in my mouth.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.80,0:13:24.92,Default,,0,0,0,,托尼是他的幻想好友\N{\rEng}Tony's his imaginary friend.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.10,0:13:31.13,Default,,0,0,0,,你现在能不能张开嘴  让我见见托尼\N{\rEng}If you were to open your mouth now, could I see Tony?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.35,0:13:33.51,Default,,0,0,0,,不行\N{\rEng}No.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.20,0:13:35.39,Default,,0,0,0,,为什么\N{\rEng}Why not?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.69,0:13:38.32,Default,,0,0,0,,因为他藏起来了\N{\rEng}Because he hides.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.29,0:13:40.59,Default,,0,0,0,,他去哪了\N{\rEng}Where does he go?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.15,0:13:43.52,Default,,0,0,0,,进我肚子里了\N{\rEng}To my stomach.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.86,0:13:48.69,Default,,0,0,0,,托尼让你做过什么事吗\N{\rEng}Does Tony ever tell you to do things?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.90,0:13:55.13,Default,,0,0,0,,我不想再聊托尼了\N{\rEng}I don't want to talk about Tony anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.43,0:13:57.55,Default,,0,0,0,,好吧\N{\rEng}Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.25,0:13:59.35,Default,,0,0,0,,没关系\N{\rEng}That's fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.39,0:14:01.62,Default,,0,0,0,,好了  丹尼\N{\rEng}All right, Danny.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.02,0:14:05.61,Default,,0,0,0,,我想请你帮我个忙\N{\rEng}I'm going to ask you to do me a favor
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.99,0:14:09.65,Default,,0,0,0,,今天都乖乖地躺在床上  好吗\N{\rEng}and stay quietly in bed for the rest of the day. Okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.65,0:14:10.76,Default,,0,0,0,,一定要这样吗\N{\rEng}Do I have to?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.88,0:14:13.20,Default,,0,0,0,,是的  我希望你听话\N{\rEng}Yes. I'd like you to.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.34,0:14:16.32,Default,,0,0,0,,我们去另一个房间聊一会儿\N{\rEng}We're going in the other room for a few minutes and talk.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.32,0:14:18.02,Default,,0,0,0,,我会回来看你的\N{\rEng}I'll come back and check on you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.16,0:14:19.49,Default,,0,0,0,,-好吗  -好的\N{\rEng}-Okay?  - Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.49,0:14:20.45,Default,,0,0,0,,再见\N{\rEng}Bye.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.99,0:14:28.95,Default,,0,0,0,,-我们到客厅去吧  -好的\N{\rEng}- Shall we go into the living room? - Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.19,0:14:34.60,Default,,0,0,0,,-请坐  -谢谢\N{\rEng}- Please. - Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.79,0:14:43.42,Default,,0,0,0,,托伦斯夫人  我觉得你无需担心\N{\rEng}Mrs. Torrance, I don't think you have anything to worry about.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.43,0:14:47.12,Default,,0,0,0,,我非常肯定丹尼的身体没有任何问题\N{\rEng}I'm quite sure there's nothing physically wrong with Danny.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.21,0:14:49.35,Default,,0,0,0,,是吗\N{\rEng}Yeah?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.21,0:14:55.26,Default,,0,0,0,,他现在看上去没有任何问题\N{\rEng}He seems absolutely fine now.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.26,0:14:56.73,Default,,0,0,0,,但你真该看看他之前的样子\N{\rEng}But you should've seen him.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.19,0:14:58.31,Default,,0,0,0,,我懂的\N{\rEng}I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.37,0:15:00.25,Default,,0,0,0,,小孩出点事能把做父母的吓死\N{\rEng}Kids can scare you to death.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.25,0:15:03.38,Default,,0,0,0,,但相信我  这种突然的发作一点也不罕见\N{\rEng}But believe me, these episodes are not at all uncommon.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.38,0:15:05.55,Default,,0,0,0,,虽然看起来很糟  但实际情况并非如此\N{\rEng}And they look much worse than they are.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.46,0:15:09.08,Default,,0,0,0,,不过他到底是怎么回事\N{\rEng}But what was the matter with him?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.26,0:15:10.77,Default,,0,0,0,,托伦斯夫人  很多时候\N{\rEng}Mrs. Torrance, Most of the time,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.77,0:15:13.45,Default,,0,0,0,,孩子的这种突然发作都无法解释\N{\rEng}these episodes with kids are never explained.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.62,0:15:18.61,Default,,0,0,0,,通常是由情感因素引起的  很少会再次出现\N{\rEng}They're brought on by emotional factors and rarely occur again.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.31,0:15:22.50,Default,,0,0,0,,那更像是自我催眠\N{\rEng}They're more akin to autohypnosis
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.52,0:15:25.08,Default,,0,0,0,,一种自发式的催眠行为\N{\rEng}A kind of self-induced trance.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.63,0:15:28.39,Default,,0,0,0,,如果再发生  尽管我觉得不大可能\N{\rEng}If it reoccurs, which I doubt
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.56,0:15:31.36,Default,,0,0,0,,可以考虑做一些检查\N{\rEng}we can always think about having some tests done.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.16,0:15:33.27,Default,,0,0,0,,不了  谢谢你\N{\rEng}No, thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.39,0:15:36.21,Default,,0,0,0,,我相信你说得对\N{\rEng}I'm sure you're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.11,0:15:40.48,Default,,0,0,0,,你在博尔德待了很久吗  托伦斯夫人\N{\rEng}Have you been in Boulder long, Mrs. Torrance?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.71,0:15:43.21,Default,,0,0,0,,刚来大约三个月\N{\rEng}Only about three months.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.21,0:15:46.18,Default,,0,0,0,,我们是从佛蒙特州来的  我丈夫以前在那教书\N{\rEng}We're from Vermont. My husband was teaching school there.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.51,0:15:52.13,Default,,0,0,0,,丹尼那位幻想好友的出现...\N{\rEng}Did the appearance of Danny's imaginary friend...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.77,0:15:53.78,Default,,0,0,0,,托尼\N{\rEng}Tony.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.78,0:15:55.36,Default,,0,0,0,,托尼的初次出现\N{\rEng}Did Tony's first appearance
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.36,0:15:57.84,Default,,0,0,0,,是否恰好是你们搬来这里的时候\N{\rEng}happen to coincide with your arrival here?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.04,0:16:00.21,Default,,0,0,0,,不是\N{\rEng}No.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.93,0:16:02.03,Default,,0,0,0,,我想想...\N{\rEng}Let's see...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.89,0:16:04.76,Default,,0,0,0,,我想丹尼开始跟托尼说话\N{\rEng}I guess Danny started talking to Tony
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.76,0:16:07.91,Default,,0,0,0,,大约是在我们送他进幼儿园的时候\N{\rEng}about the time we put him in nursery school.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.79,0:16:10.60,Default,,0,0,0,,他对于学校生活适应得好吗\N{\rEng}Did he adjust well to school?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.02,0:16:13.16,Default,,0,0,0,,不好\N{\rEng}No.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.27,0:16:15.19,Default,,0,0,0,,起先他不太喜欢上学\N{\rEng}He didn't like it too much at first.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.37,0:16:18.69,Default,,0,0,0,,然后他受了伤  所以我们有阵子没让他去上学\N{\rEng}Then he had an injury, so we kept him out for a while and
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.40,0:16:21.21,Default,,0,0,0,,没错  差不多就是那时候\N{\rEng}Yeah, I guess that's about
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.21,0:16:23.82,Default,,0,0,0,,我发现他在跟托尼说话的\N{\rEng}when I first noticed he was talking to Tony.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.00,0:16:27.03,Default,,0,0,0,,他受了什么伤\N{\rEng}What sort of injury did he have?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.35,0:16:29.86,Default,,0,0,0,,他的肩膀脱臼了\N{\rEng}He dislocated his shoulder.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.74,0:16:32.67,Default,,0,0,0,,怎么弄的\N{\rEng}How did he manage to do that?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.63,0:16:39.69,Default,,0,0,0,,就是小孩子常见的那种情况  你懂的\N{\rEng}It was just one of those things, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.69,0:16:41.39,Default,,0,0,0,,纯粹是意外\N{\rEng}Purely an accident.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.66,0:16:46.30,Default,,0,0,0,,我丈夫一直在酗酒\N{\rEng}My husband had been drinking and
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.30,0:16:48.49,Default,,0,0,0,,他那天晚回来三个多小时\N{\rEng}he came home about three hours late.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.31,0:16:53.61,Default,,0,0,0,,那晚他心情不太好\N{\rEng}So he wasn't exactly in the greatest mood that night.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.62,0:16:59.57,Default,,0,0,0,,丹尼把书本和作业纸弄得满屋子都是\N{\rEng}And Danny had scattered some of his school papers all over the room
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.57,0:17:03.56,Default,,0,0,0,,我丈夫抓住他的胳膊  把他拉开\N{\rEng}and my husband grabbed his arm to pull him away from them.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.09,0:17:06.73,Default,,0,0,0,,就是父母常会对小孩做的那种事\N{\rEng}It's just the sort of thing you do 100 times with a child
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.73,0:17:08.97,Default,,0,0,0,,在公园里  或街上  都很常见\N{\rEng}you know, in a park or in the street.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.52,0:17:13.53,Default,,0,0,0,,但那一次\N{\rEng}But on this particular occasion
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.53,0:17:16.12,Default,,0,0,0,,我丈夫用力过猛\N{\rEng}my husband just used too much strength
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.12,0:17:19.12,Default,,0,0,0,,伤到了丹尼的胳膊\N{\rEng}and he injured Danny's arm.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.78,0:17:24.87,Default,,0,0,0,,不过  这事还是有些好处的\N{\rEng}Anyway, something good did come out of it all
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.87,0:17:25.97,Default,,0,0,0,,因为他说\N{\rEng}because he said:
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.46,0:17:29.28,Default,,0,0,0,,"温蒂  我再也不会喝一滴酒了\N{\rEng}"Wendy, I'm never going to touch another drop.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.38,0:17:31.30,Default,,0,0,0,,如果我再喝  你就离开我"\N{\rEng}And if I do, you can leave me. "
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.50,0:17:33.13,Default,,0,0,0,,然后他就再没喝过酒了\N{\rEng}And he didn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.13,0:17:37.20,Default,,0,0,0,,他五个月没有沾酒了\N{\rEng}He hasn't had any alcohol in 5 months.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.93,0:17:41.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8\pos(192,152)}{\fn方正兰亭中黑_GBK\fs30\b0\bord0\shad0\3c&H2F2F2F&\c&HFFFFFF&}停  业  日
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.87,0:18:03.99,Default,,0,0,0,,天呐\N{\rEng}Boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.58,0:18:08.62,Default,,0,0,0,,我们一定在很高的地方  空气都感觉很不同\N{\rEng}We must really be high up. The air feels so different.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.30,0:18:15.35,Default,,0,0,0,,爸爸\N{\rEng}Dad?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.05,0:18:17.18,Default,,0,0,0,,什么事\N{\rEng}Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.33,0:18:19.59,Default,,0,0,0,,我饿了\N{\rEng}I'm hungry.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.97,0:18:24.47,Default,,0,0,0,,你应该吃早餐的\N{\rEng}You should've eaten your breakfast.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.44,0:18:28.30,Default,,0,0,0,,等到了酒店我就给你弄东西吃  好吗\N{\rEng}We'll get you something as soon as we get to the hotel. Okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.57,0:18:29.83,Default,,0,0,0,,好吧  妈妈\N{\rEng}Okay, Mom.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.44,0:18:35.34,Default,,0,0,0,,唐纳大队不就是在这里被雪困住的吗\N{\rEng}Wasn't it around here that the Donner party got snowbound?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.49,0:18:40.70,Default,,0,0,0,,我觉得应该是更靠西的地方  在内华达山脉\N{\rEng}I think that was farther west, in the Sierras.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.47,0:18:44.51,Default,,0,0,0,,什么是唐纳大队\N{\rEng}What was the Donner party?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.84,0:18:50.72,Default,,0,0,0,,是西部大开发时期的一群移民\N{\rEng}They were a party of settlers in covered wagon times.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.32,0:18:54.40,Default,,0,0,0,,有年冬天  他们被大雪困在了大山里\N{\rEng}They got snowbound one winter in the mountains.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.76,0:18:58.70,Default,,0,0,0,,为了活命  他们不得不靠吃人肉为生\N{\rEng}They had to resort to cannibalism in order to stay alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.14,0:19:02.81,Default,,0,0,0,,你是说他们把自己人给吃了\N{\rEng}You mean they ate each other up?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.23,0:19:06.33,Default,,0,0,0,,只有这样才能生存下来\N{\rEng}They had to in order to survive.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.57,0:19:07.69,Default,,0,0,0,,杰克\N{\rEng}Jack.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.01,0:19:09.27,Default,,0,0,0,,别担心  妈妈\N{\rEng}Don't worry, Mom.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.27,0:19:13.33,Default,,0,0,0,,我知道关于食人的事  我在电视上看过\N{\rEng}I know all about cannibalism. I saw it on TV.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.80,0:19:16.30,Default,,0,0,0,,瞧吧  没事的\N{\rEng}See, it's okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.66,0:19:18.75,Default,,0,0,0,,他在电视上看过\N{\rEng}He saw it on the television.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.74,0:19:51.88,Default,,0,0,0,,-飞机什么时候起飞  -8点半\N{\rEng}- What time does the plane leave? - 8:30.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.98,0:19:54.77,Default,,0,0,0,,那我们还有足够的时间把各项事宜再过一遍\N{\rEng}That gives us plenty of time to go over everything first.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.77,0:19:56.59,Default,,0,0,0,,-再见  乌尔曼先生  -再见\N{\rEng}- Goodbye, Mr. Ullman. - Bye.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.91,0:20:00.01,Default,,0,0,0,,早上好  杰克  希望没让你等太久\N{\rEng}Good morning, Jack. I hope you haven't been waiting too long.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.29,0:20:03.07,Default,,0,0,0,,没关系  刚好让我们有时间吃点东西\N{\rEng}No problem. In fact we had time to grab a bite to eat.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.07,0:20:05.95,Default,,0,0,0,,那就好  很高兴你们在厨房关停前赶到了\N{\rEng}Good. Glad you made it before they shut down the kitchen.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.98,0:20:07.91,Default,,0,0,0,,-你好  -你的家人到处看过了吗\N{\rEng}- Hi. - Is your family having a look around?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.16,0:20:11.09,Default,,0,0,0,,没有  我儿子发现了游戏室\N{\rEng}No, my son's discovered the games room.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.72,0:20:14.07,Default,,0,0,0,,-行李都拿进来了吧  -就在那边\N{\rEng}- Has your luggage been brought in? - Right there.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.07,0:20:15.11,Default,,0,0,0,,好的\N{\rEng}Oh, fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.94,0:20:17.66,Default,,0,0,0,,鉴于我们今天要带你了解不少地方\N{\rEng}In view of all the ground we have to cover today
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.66,0:20:19.60,Default,,0,0,0,,我建议我们先快速看一下你们的公寓\N{\rEng}I suggest we have a quick look at your apartment
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.60,0:20:21.36,Default,,0,0,0,,然后立刻开始\N{\rEng}and get started straight away.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.43,0:20:23.05,Default,,0,0,0,,比尔  你能安排先把托伦斯一家的东西\N{\rEng}Bill, would you have the Torrances' things
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.05,0:20:23.97,Default,,0,0,0,,送到他们的公寓去吗\N{\rEng}brought to their apartment.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.97,0:20:26.31,Default,,0,0,0,,-好的  -我最好先叫一下我的家人\N{\rEng}- Fine. - I'd better collect my family first.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.31,0:20:27.67,Default,,0,0,0,,好的\N{\rEng}Oh, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.26,0:20:37.70,Default,,0,0,0,,这里是我们的科罗拉多休闲室\N{\rEng}This is our Colorado Lounge.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.32,0:20:40.03,Default,,0,0,0,,真漂亮\N{\rEng}It's beautiful.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.62,0:20:42.43,Default,,0,0,0,,我的天啊\N{\rEng}My God!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.70,0:20:45.43,Default,,0,0,0,,这里真是美极了  不是吗  亲爱的\N{\rEng}This place is fantastic, isn't it, hon?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.43,0:20:46.81,Default,,0,0,0,,当然\N{\rEng}It sure is.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.06,0:20:49.50,Default,,0,0,0,,我从没见过这样的东西\N{\rEng}I've never seen anything like this before.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.45,0:20:53.64,Default,,0,0,0,,这些印第安风格的设计都是真品吗\N{\rEng}Are all these Indian designs authentic?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.64,0:20:58.62,Default,,0,0,0,,好像主要是根据纳瓦霍族和阿帕切族的图案设计的\N{\rEng}I believe they're based mainly on Navajo and Apache motifs.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.94,0:21:00.57,Default,,0,0,0,,真的太美了\N{\rEng}They're really gorgeous.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.83,0:21:01.47,Default,,0,0,0,,实际上\N{\rEng}As a matter of fact
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.47,0:21:04.62,Default,,0,0,0,,这可能是我见过的最美的酒店了\N{\rEng}this is probably the most gorgeous hotel I've ever seen.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.94,0:21:08.53,Default,,0,0,0,,这家老酒店有着辉煌的历史\N{\rEng}This old place has had an illustrious past.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.70,0:21:12.07,Default,,0,0,0,,在其全盛时期  曾住满了社会名流\N{\rEng}In its heyday, it was one of the stopping place for the jet setters
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.07,0:21:15.05,Default,,0,0,0,,即便那时大家都还不知道社会名流是什么意思\N{\rEng}even before anybody knew what a jet set was.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.28,0:21:17.96,Default,,0,0,0,,有四位总统曾在此住过\N{\rEng}We had four presidents who stayed here.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.59,0:21:20.08,Default,,0,0,0,,很多电影明星\N{\rEng}Lots of movie stars.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.08,0:21:21.20,Default,,0,0,0,,有皇室的人吗\N{\rEng}Royalty?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.97,0:21:23.35,Default,,0,0,0,,都是最上层的人物\N{\rEng}All the best people.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.50,0:22:18.69,Default,,0,0,0,,这里是酒店的员工宿舍侧楼\N{\rEng}This is the staff wing of the hotel.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.11,0:22:22.92,Default,,0,0,0,,其它卧室冬天都不供暖\N{\rEng}None of the other bedrooms are heated during the winter.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.61,0:22:26.10,Default,,0,0,0,,-再见  乌尔曼先生  -再见  姑娘们\N{\rEng}- Goodbye, Mr. Ullman. - Goodbye, girls.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.81,0:22:29.11,Default,,0,0,0,,这就是你们的住处\N{\rEng}And here are your quarters.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.26,0:22:32.02,Default,,0,0,0,,起居室  卧室  洗手间\N{\rEng}Living room, bedroom, bathroom.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.02,0:22:34.09,Default,,0,0,0,,还有给你们的儿子住的小房间\N{\rEng}And a small bedroom for your son.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.13,0:22:39.89,Default,,0,0,0,,非常适合小孩子\N{\rEng}Perfect for a child.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.89,0:22:41.18,Default,,0,0,0,,-是啊  -是的\N{\rEng}- Yeah. - Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.40,0:22:50.81,Default,,0,0,0,,好了  这房子独门独户  不用跟别人共用设施\N{\rEng}Well, then. Place is very nicely self-contained.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.03,0:22:52.31,Default,,0,0,0,,也好打理\N{\rEng}Easy to keep.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.34,0:22:56.42,Default,,0,0,0,,舒适\N{\rEng}Cozy.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.56,0:22:58.51,Default,,0,0,0,,是的  非常适合一家人居住\N{\rEng}Yes, very cozy for a family.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.12,0:23:00.94,Default,,0,0,0,,如果你们想换个环境\N{\rEng}If you feel like spreading out
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.94,0:23:03.31,Default,,0,0,0,,酒店的其他地方也随便你们住\N{\rEng}you have the rest of the hotel to move around in.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.33,0:23:07.36,Default,,0,0,0,,这里真是...\N{\rEng}Well, it's very...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.33,0:23:09.48,Default,,0,0,0,,太有家的感觉了\N{\rEng}homey.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.87,0:23:11.01,Default,,0,0,0,,是啊\N{\rEng}Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.51,0:23:14.90,Default,,0,0,0,,这里是我们著名的树篱迷宫\N{\rEng}This is our famous hedge maze.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.99,0:23:19.08,Default,,0,0,0,,算是这里的一处独特景点吧  墙有13英尺高\N{\rEng}It's quite an attraction here. The walls are 13 feet high
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.52,0:23:21.91,Default,,0,0,0,,树篱和酒店一样历史悠久\N{\rEng}and the hedge is as old as the hotel itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.91,0:23:22.99,Default,,0,0,0,,很好玩\N{\rEng}A lot of fun,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.66,0:23:24.73,Default,,0,0,0,,但我一般是不会进去的\N{\rEng}but I wouldn't want to go in there
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.73,0:23:27.52,Default,,0,0,0,,除非我有一小时的空闲时间用来找出路\N{\rEng}unless I had an hour to spare to find my way out.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.21,0:23:31.11,Default,,0,0,0,,眺望酒店是什么时候建成的\N{\rEng}When was the Overlook built?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.28,0:23:34.67,Default,,0,0,0,,1907年开始建造\N{\rEng}Construction started in 1907.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.80,0:23:36.53,Default,,0,0,0,,1909年完工\N{\rEng}It was finished in 1909.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.93,0:23:39.77,Default,,0,0,0,,这里曾经是一座印第安坟场\N{\rEng}The site's supposed to be on an Indian burial ground.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.77,0:23:41.71,Default,,0,0,0,,据我所知  他们在施工时\N{\rEng}And I believe they actually had to repel
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.71,0:23:44.11,Default,,0,0,0,,不得不打退几次印第安人的袭击\N{\rEng}a few Indian attacks as they were building it.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.13,0:23:46.83,Default,,0,0,0,,那是我们的雪地车\N{\rEng}That's our Snowcat.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.75,0:23:49.22,Default,,0,0,0,,你们都会开车吗\N{\rEng}Can you both drive a car?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.22,0:23:50.28,Default,,0,0,0,,会\N{\rEng}Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.28,0:23:51.20,Default,,0,0,0,,那就好\N{\rEng}That's fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.37,0:23:54.24,Default,,0,0,0,,因为驾驶雪地车基本和开车一样\N{\rEng}Because basically the Snowcat operates very much like a car.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.24,0:23:56.24,Default,,0,0,0,,很快就能掌握诀窍了\N{\rEng}It won't take you long to get the hang of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.85,0:23:58.57,Default,,0,0,0,,事实上\N{\rEng}As a matter of fact,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.02,0:24:02.10,Default,,0,0,0,,我们去年从芝加哥请了一位设计师\N{\rEng}we brought a decorator in from Chicago just last year
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.10,0:24:04.26,Default,,0,0,0,,给酒店的这一部分进行重新装修\N{\rEng}to refurbish this part of the hotel.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.78,0:24:06.73,Default,,0,0,0,,他确实装修得很不错\N{\rEng}He sure did a beautiful job.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.94,0:24:08.96,Default,,0,0,0,,粉色和金色是我最喜欢的颜色\N{\rEng}Pink and gold are my favorite colors.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.13,0:24:12.21,Default,,0,0,0,,这里是我们的金色舞厅\N{\rEng}Well, this is our Gold Ballroom.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.10,0:24:15.29,Default,,0,0,0,,我就说嘛\N{\rEng}I'll say!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.49,0:24:18.90,Default,,0,0,0,,这里可以轻松容纳三百人\N{\rEng}We can accommodate up to 300 people here very comfortably.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.80,0:24:22.95,Default,,0,0,0,,天呐  我们可以在这里办一场盛大的派对\N{\rEng}Boy, I bet you we could really have a good party in this room.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.35,0:24:24.89,Default,,0,0,0,,恐怕你们办不起来多么盛大的派对\N{\rEng}I'm afraid you won't do too well here
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.89,0:24:26.84,Default,,0,0,0,,除非你们能自带物资\N{\rEng}unless you brought supplies.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.87,0:24:30.16,Default,,0,0,0,,我们停业时  会将酒全部撤走\N{\rEng}We always remove the booze from the premises when we shut down.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.16,0:24:33.08,Default,,0,0,0,,那可以减少我们通常得承担的保险费用\N{\rEng}That reduces the insurance we normally have to carry.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.41,0:24:34.81,Default,,0,0,0,,我们不喝酒\N{\rEng}We don't drink.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.96,0:24:36.36,Default,,0,0,0,,那你们走运了\N{\rEng}Then you're in luck.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.49,0:24:40.66,Default,,0,0,0,,迪克  快过来跟托伦斯夫妇打个招呼\N{\rEng}Dick, come on over and say hello to Mr. and Mrs. Torrance.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:40.66,0:24:42.89,Default,,0,0,0,,这位是迪克·哈洛兰  我们的主厨\N{\rEng}This is Dick Hallorann, our head chef.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:42.89,0:24:44.99,Default,,0,0,0,,-哈洛兰先生  我是杰克  -很高兴认识你  杰克\N{\rEng}- Mr. Hallorann, I'm Jack. - Glad to meet you, Jack.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:44.99,0:24:45.93,Default,,0,0,0,,这位是我妻子  温妮芙德\N{\rEng}This is my wife, Winifred.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:45.93,0:24:47.21,Default,,0,0,0,,-很高兴认识你  温妮芙德  -很高兴认识你\N{\rEng}- Glad to meet you, Winifred. - Nice to meet you.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:47.21,0:24:50.48,Default,,0,0,0,,托伦斯夫妇今年冬天会替我们照料眺望酒店\N{\rEng}The Torrances are gonna take care of the Overlook for us this winter.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:50.78,0:24:54.62,Default,,0,0,0,,太好了  你们目前觉得这个酒店怎么样\N{\rEng}That's just great. How do you folks like our hotel so far?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:54.62,0:24:56.05,Default,,0,0,0,,简直棒极了\N{\rEng}It's just wonderful.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:56.39,0:24:57.57,Default,,0,0,0,,嗨  丹尼\N{\rEng}Hi, Danny!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:58.76,0:25:01.12,Default,,0,0,0,,我发现他在外面找你们\N{\rEng}I found him outside looking for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:01.74,0:25:05.22,Default,,0,0,0,,丹  你厌倦轰炸宇宙了吗\N{\rEng}Dan, did you get tired of bombing the universe?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:05.45,0:25:06.56,Default,,0,0,0,,是的\N{\rEng}Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:06.96,0:25:08.21,Default,,0,0,0,,过来\N{\rEng}Come on over here.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:08.21,0:25:09.97,Default,,0,0,0,,-谢谢  -谢谢你  苏希\N{\rEng}- Thanks. - Thank you, Susie.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:10.05,0:25:11.64,Default,,0,0,0,,迪克  如果你准备好了\N{\rEng}Dick, if you're ready to do it now,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:11.64,0:25:14.45,Default,,0,0,0,,我觉得你可以带托伦斯夫人去看看厨房\N{\rEng}I think it'd be a good idea if you could show Mrs. Torrance the kitchen
Dialogue: 0,0:25:14.45,0:25:16.28,Default,,0,0,0,,我再继续跟杰克交代交代\N{\rEng}while I continue on with Jack.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:16.28,0:25:18.96,Default,,0,0,0,,非常乐意  这边请  托伦斯夫人\N{\rEng}It would be a pleasure. Right this way, Mrs. Torrance.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:18.96,0:25:20.73,Default,,0,0,0,,太棒了  待会儿见  亲爱的\N{\rEng}Great. See you later, hon.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:20.73,0:25:21.91,Default,,0,0,0,,回见  亲爱的\N{\rEng}Bye, darling.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:23.79,0:25:25.75,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8\pos(115.5,44)}{\fn方正黑体_GBK\fs18\b1\bord0\shad\3c&H2F2F2F&\c&HB8B8E7&}安全出口  不得堵塞
Dialogue: 0,0:25:24.46,0:25:28.08,Default,,0,0,0,,托伦斯夫人  你丈夫介绍你时  叫你温妮芙德\N{\rEng}Mrs. Torrance, your husband introduced you as Winifred.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:28.08,0:25:30.58,Default,,0,0,0,,那我应该叫你温妮还是芙莱蒂\N{\rEng}Now, are you a "Winnie," or a "Freddie"?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:30.73,0:25:31.96,Default,,0,0,0,,叫我温蒂就行\N{\rEng}I'm a Wendy.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:32.24,0:25:35.51,Default,,0,0,0,,温蒂啊  真好听  再好听不过了\N{\rEng}Oh, Wendy. That's nice. That's the prettiest.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:35.60,0:25:37.41,Default,,0,0,0,,天啊  这厨房太气派了\N{\rEng}God, this is the kitchen, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:37.41,0:25:38.81,Default,,0,0,0,,没错  正是\N{\rEng}Yeah, this is it.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:39.17,0:25:41.77,Default,,0,0,0,,你觉得怎么样  丹尼  够大吗\N{\rEng}How do you like it, Danny? Is it big enough for you?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:41.77,0:25:44.76,Default,,0,0,0,,是的  这是我见过的最大的地方\N{\rEng}Yeah. It's the biggest place I ever seen.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:45.48,0:25:47.99,Default,,0,0,0,,是啊  这里简直就是一个巨大的迷宫\N{\rEng}Yeah, this whole place is such an enormous maze.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:47.99,0:25:48.90,Default,,0,0,0,,我觉得每次进来这儿\N{\rEng}I feel like I'll have to
Dialogue: 0,0:25:48.90,0:25:51.16,Default,,0,0,0,,都得撒面包屑  标记返回的路\N{\rEng}leave a trail of breadcrumbs every time I come in.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:52.41,0:25:54.54,Default,,0,0,0,,别灰心  托伦斯夫人\N{\rEng}Don't let it get you down, Mrs. Torrance.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:54.54,0:25:57.17,Default,,0,0,0,,这里是很大  但也不过是个厨房而已\N{\rEng}It's big, but it still ain't nothing but a kitchen.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:57.21,0:25:59.50,Default,,0,0,0,,而且这里的很多东西你连碰都不用碰\N{\rEng}And a lot of this stuff you'll never have to touch.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:59.50,0:26:01.87,Default,,0,0,0,,就算真让我碰  我也不知道怎么用\N{\rEng}I wouldn't know what to do with it if I did.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:02.00,0:26:05.33,Default,,0,0,0,,至少你们丝毫不用担心食物的问题\N{\rEng}Well, one thing for sure, you don't have to worry about food.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:05.33,0:26:08.35,Default,,0,0,0,,因为你们一家可以在这里吃上一整年\N{\rEng}because ou folks could eat up here a whole year
Dialogue: 0,0:26:08.35,0:26:10.21,Default,,0,0,0,,菜单都不带重样的\N{\rEng}and never have the same menu twice.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:10.21,0:26:13.92,Default,,0,0,0,,这里是我们的步入式冷冻室\N{\rEng}Now, right here is our walk-in freezer.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:14.71,0:26:17.33,Default,,0,0,0,,我们将所有肉类都储存在这里\N{\rEng}Now, this is where we keep all of our meat.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:17.78,0:26:19.97,Default,,0,0,0,,15扇肋排\N{\rEng}You got 15 rib roasts...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:20.00,0:26:22.33,Default,,0,0,0,,30袋汉堡肉  每袋重10磅\N{\rEng}30 ten-pound bags of hamburger.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:22.33,0:26:25.63,Default,,0,0,0,,12只火鸡  大概40只鸡\N{\rEng}We got 12 turkeys, about 40 chickens...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:25.63,0:26:28.99,Default,,0,0,0,,50块西冷牛排  24卷猪排\N{\rEng}50 sirloin steaks, two dozen of pork roast...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:28.99,0:26:32.12,Default,,0,0,0,,还有20只羊腿  你喜欢羊肉吗  博士\N{\rEng}and 20 legs of lamb. Do you like lamb, Doc?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:32.12,0:26:33.86,Default,,0,0,0,,-不喜欢  -不喜欢吗\N{\rEng}- No. - You don't?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:33.86,0:26:35.67,Default,,0,0,0,,那你最喜欢吃什么\N{\rEng}Well, what's your favorite food, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:35.67,0:26:37.21,Default,,0,0,0,,炸薯条配番茄酱\N{\rEng}French fries and ketchup.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:38.29,0:26:40.55,Default,,0,0,0,,那也没问题  博士\N{\rEng}Well, I think we can manage that too, Doc.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:40.55,0:26:42.18,Default,,0,0,0,,跟我来  小心脚下\N{\rEng}Come along, now. Watch your step.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:45.93,0:26:47.23,Default,,0,0,0,,哈洛兰先生\N{\rEng}Mr. Hallorann...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:48.88,0:26:50.71,Default,,0,0,0,,你怎么知道我们叫他博士\N{\rEng}how'd you know we call him Doc?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:50.71,0:26:51.55,Default,,0,0,0,,你说什么\N{\rEng}Beg your pardon?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:51.74,0:26:54.78,Default,,0,0,0,,「博士」  你刚才两次那样叫丹尼\N{\rEng}Doc. You called Danny "Doc" twice just now.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:54.96,0:26:56.77,Default,,0,0,0,,-是吗  -是啊\N{\rEng}- I did? - Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:57.10,0:26:58.42,Default,,0,0,0,,我们有时候叫他博士\N{\rEng}We call him Doc sometimes,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:58.42,0:27:00.47,Default,,0,0,0,,就像兔八哥卡通片里的博士\N{\rEng}like in the Bugs Bunny cartoons.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:00.47,0:27:01.97,Default,,0,0,0,,但你是怎么知道的\N{\rEng}But how did you know that?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:01.97,0:27:04.72,Default,,0,0,0,,我想可能是因为我听见你那样叫过他吧\N{\rEng}Well, I guess I probably heard you call him that.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:04.72,0:27:07.13,Default,,0,0,0,,有可能  但我真不记得\N{\rEng}Well, it's possible. But I honestly don't remember
Dialogue: 0,0:27:07.13,0:27:09.46,Default,,0,0,0,,我们见面之后  我那样叫过他\N{\rEng}calling him that since we've been with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:09.58,0:27:11.98,Default,,0,0,0,,他看起来就像个博士  对不对\N{\rEng}Well, anyway, he looks like a Doc, doesn't he?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:13.27,0:27:14.42,Default,,0,0,0,,「还好吗  博士」\N{\rEng}What's up, Doc?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:16.39,0:27:18.80,Default,,0,0,0,,好了  这里是储藏室\N{\rEng}Now, this is the storeroom.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:20.40,0:27:21.74,Default,,0,0,0,,托伦斯夫人  在这里面\N{\rEng}In here, Mrs. Torrance,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:21.74,0:27:25.49,Default,,0,0,0,,存放着我们所有的干货和罐头\N{\rEng}is where we keep all the dried goods and the canned goods.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:25.49,0:27:28.07,Default,,0,0,0,,有水果罐头  蔬菜罐头\N{\rEng}We got canned fruits and vegetables...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:28.07,0:27:32.08,Default,,0,0,0,,鱼罐头  肉罐头  各种冷吃热吃麦片\N{\rEng}canned fish and meats, hot and cold cereals.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:32.08,0:27:35.41,Default,,0,0,0,,博斯特麦片  玉米片  膨化甜麦片\N{\rEng}Post Toasties, Corn Flakes, Sugar Puffs...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:35.41,0:27:39.70,Default,,0,0,0,,脆米麦片  燕麦片  脆小麦麦片  还有麦乳\N{\rEng}Rice Krispies, oatmeal, Wheatena and Cream of Wheat.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:39.70,0:27:42.31,Default,,0,0,0,,几十罐黑糖蜜\N{\rEng}You got a dozen jugs of black molasses.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:42.31,0:27:45.11,Default,,0,0,0,,60盒奶粉\N{\rEng}We got 60 boxes of dried milk...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:53.28,0:27:55.57,Default,,0,0,0,,你想吃冰激凌吗  博士\N{\rEng}How'd you like some ice cream, Doc?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:58.21,0:28:00.21,Default,,0,0,0,,饼干  手指卷面包\N{\rEng}Sociables, finger rolls...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:00.21,0:28:01.99,Default,,0,0,0,,还有七种其他的\N{\rEng}and 7 kinds of what have you.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:01.99,0:28:05.79,Default,,0,0,0,,有桃干  杏干\N{\rEng}Now, we've got dried peaches, dried apricots...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:05.79,0:28:08.55,Default,,0,0,0,,葡萄干还有西梅干\N{\rEng}dried raisins and dried prunes.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:08.55,0:28:10.16,Default,,0,0,0,,托伦斯夫人\N{\rEng}You know, Mrs. Torrance,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:10.17,0:28:12.98,Default,,0,0,0,,想过得快乐  就得保持日常生活细节不变\N{\rEng}you got to keep regular if you want to be happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:16.30,0:28:18.15,Default,,0,0,0,,-参观得怎么样  -很好\N{\rEng}- How're you getting on? - Just fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:18.15,0:28:20.52,Default,,0,0,0,,迪克  能让托伦斯夫人跟我们来一下吗\N{\rEng}Dick, can we borrow Mrs. Torrance for a few minutes?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:20.52,0:28:22.23,Default,,0,0,0,,我们正要去地下室\N{\rEng}We're on our way through to the basement.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:22.23,0:28:24.00,Default,,0,0,0,,我保证不会很久的\N{\rEng}I promise we won't keep her very long.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:24.00,0:28:27.46,Default,,0,0,0,,没问题  乌尔曼先生  我们正要去吃冰激凌\N{\rEng}No problem, Mr. Ullman. I was just getting to the ice cream.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:27.47,0:28:29.90,Default,,0,0,0,,-你喜欢冰激凌吧  博士  -喜欢\N{\rEng}- You like ice cream, Doc? - Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:30.08,0:28:31.35,Default,,0,0,0,,我想也是\N{\rEng}I thought you did.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:31.36,0:28:32.25,Default,,0,0,0,,你们不介意\N{\rEng}You folks don't mind
Dialogue: 0,0:28:32.25,0:28:34.56,Default,,0,0,0,,我带丹尼吃点冰激凌  边吃边等你们吧\N{\rEng}if I give Danny some ice cream while we waiting for you?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:34.56,0:28:36.64,Default,,0,0,0,,-当然不  -不介意\N{\rEng}- Not at all. - No, we don't mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:36.64,0:28:38.40,Default,,0,0,0,,-好  -你觉得好不好  博士\N{\rEng}- Good. - Sound good to you, Doc?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:38.40,0:28:40.74,Default,,0,0,0,,-好  -好  你要乖乖的哦\N{\rEng}- Yeah. - Okay, you behave yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:44.12,0:28:46.19,Default,,0,0,0,,你喜欢什么冰激凌  博士\N{\rEng}What kind of ice cream do you like, Doc?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:46.19,0:28:47.26,Default,,0,0,0,,巧克力的\N{\rEng}Chocolate.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:47.26,0:28:49.86,Default,,0,0,0,,那我们就吃巧克力口味的  来吧  孩子\N{\rEng}Chocolate it shall be. Come on, son.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:54.79,0:28:57.00,Default,,0,0,0,,今天大家似乎都很忙乱啊\N{\rEng}It's amazing, how much activities going on today.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:57.00,0:28:59.33,Default,,0,0,0,,是啊  昨天客人们还有一些员工离开了\N{\rEng}Yes. Well, the guests and some of the staff left yesterday,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:59.33,0:29:01.46,Default,,0,0,0,,但停业前最后一天总是很忙乱\N{\rEng}but the last day's always hectic.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:01.46,0:29:04.87,Default,,0,0,0,,大家都想尽早上路离开\N{\rEng}Everybody wants to be on their way as early as possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:04.87,0:29:09.07,Default,,0,0,0,,等到今晚5点  就像没人在这里存在过一样\N{\rEng}By 5 o'clock tonight, you'll never know anybody was ever here.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:09.18,0:29:11.70,Default,,0,0,0,,-就像一艘幽灵船  -没错\N{\rEng}- Just like a ghost ship, huh? - Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:16.99,0:29:19.68,Default,,0,0,0,,你知道我是怎么知道你叫"博士"的吗\N{\rEng}Do you know how I knew your name was Doc?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:26.46,0:29:28.74,Default,,0,0,0,,你知道我在说什么  对吧\N{\rEng}You know what I'm talking about, don't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:35.73,0:29:38.88,Default,,0,0,0,,我记得  我小时候\N{\rEng}I can remember when I was a little boy,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:39.66,0:29:42.44,Default,,0,0,0,,我奶奶和我全程不张嘴\N{\rEng}my grandmother and I could hold conversations
Dialogue: 0,0:29:42.44,0:29:46.00,Default,,0,0,0,,就可以进行对话\N{\rEng}entirely without ever opening our mouths.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:47.33,0:29:49.44,Default,,0,0,0,,她称之为「闪灵」能力\N{\rEng}She called it "Shining."
Dialogue: 0,0:29:51.27,0:29:53.14,Default,,0,0,0,,很久以来  我以为\N{\rEng}And for a long time I thought
Dialogue: 0,0:29:53.14,0:29:56.21,Default,,0,0,0,,只有我们祖孙俩有这种能力\N{\rEng}it was just the two of us that had "the Shine" to us.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:57.30,0:29:59.97,Default,,0,0,0,,就像你可能以为只有你一个人有一样\N{\rEng}Just like you probably thought you was the only one.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:00.91,0:30:03.04,Default,,0,0,0,,但其实还有别人\N{\rEng}But there are other folks,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:03.04,0:30:06.36,Default,,0,0,0,,虽然他们自己不知道  或者不相信\N{\rEng}though mostly they don't know it, or don't believe it.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:11.41,0:30:13.31,Default,,0,0,0,,你从什么时候开始有这能力的\N{\rEng}How long have you been able to do it?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:19.05,0:30:21.13,Default,,0,0,0,,你为什么不想说呢\N{\rEng}Why don't you want to talk about it?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:26.69,0:30:28.50,Default,,0,0,0,,我不应该说出来\N{\rEng}I'm not supposed to.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:30.31,0:30:32.53,Default,,0,0,0,,谁说你不应该说出来\N{\rEng}Who says you ain't supposed to?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:36.35,0:30:37.38,Default,,0,0,0,,托尼\N{\rEng}Tony.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:39.65,0:30:40.95,Default,,0,0,0,,托尼是谁\N{\rEng}Who's Tony?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:43.86,0:30:47.10,Default,,0,0,0,,托尼是住在我嘴里的小男孩\N{\rEng}Tony's the little boy that lives in my mouth.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:49.20,0:30:52.81,Default,,0,0,0,,是托尼告诉你一些事的吗\N{\rEng}Is Tony the one that tells you things?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:54.56,0:30:55.52,Default,,0,0,0,,是的\N{\rEng}Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:57.56,0:30:59.52,Default,,0,0,0,,他是怎么告诉你那些事的\N{\rEng}How does he tell you things?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:01.75,0:31:05.98,Default,,0,0,0,,就好像我睡着以后  他给我看一些东西\N{\rEng}It's like I go to sleep, and he shows me things.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:06.24,0:31:10.09,Default,,0,0,0,,但等我醒来  我什么都记不得了\N{\rEng}But when I wake up, I can't remember everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:12.23,0:31:15.63,Default,,0,0,0,,你爸妈知道托尼的存在吗\N{\rEng}Does your mom and dad know about Tony?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:17.16,0:31:18.15,Default,,0,0,0,,知道\N{\rEng}Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:19.22,0:31:21.53,Default,,0,0,0,,他们知道他会告诉你一些事吗\N{\rEng}Do they know he tells you things?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:22.60,0:31:25.22,Default,,0,0,0,,托尼告诉我  千万别告诉他们\N{\rEng}Tony told me never to tell them.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:27.73,0:31:31.24,Default,,0,0,0,,托尼跟你说过关于这里的一些事吗\N{\rEng}Has Tony ever told you anything about this place?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:31.29,0:31:33.62,Default,,0,0,0,,关于眺望酒店\N{\rEng}About the Overlook Hotel?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:37.16,0:31:38.33,Default,,0,0,0,,我不知道\N{\rEng}I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:39.54,0:31:42.19,Default,,0,0,0,,好好想想  博士\N{\rEng}Now think real hard, Doc.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:42.22,0:31:43.25,Default,,0,0,0,,想想\N{\rEng}Think.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:46.66,0:31:49.14,Default,,0,0,0,,也许他给我看过一点\N{\rEng}Maybe he showed me something.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:50.31,0:31:52.62,Default,,0,0,0,,努力想想是什么\N{\rEng}Try to think of what it was.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:55.97,0:31:59.02,Default,,0,0,0,,哈洛兰先生  你怕这里吗\N{\rEng}Mr. Hallorann, are you scared of this place?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:01.06,0:32:04.39,Default,,0,0,0,,不  我才不怕这里\N{\rEng}No. Scared of nothing here.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:05.09,0:32:06.35,Default,,0,0,0,,只不过...\N{\rEng}It's just that...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:07.33,0:32:09.94,Default,,0,0,0,,有些地方就跟人一样\N{\rEng}you know, some places are like people.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:10.98,0:32:14.29,Default,,0,0,0,,有些有闪灵能力  有些没有\N{\rEng}Some shine and some don't.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:15.55,0:32:17.60,Default,,0,0,0,,我觉得可以说眺望酒店\N{\rEng}I guess you could say the Overlook Hotel
Dialogue: 0,0:32:17.60,0:32:20.88,Default,,0,0,0,,就有类似于闪灵的能力\N{\rEng}has something about it that's like shining.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:24.37,0:32:26.38,Default,,0,0,0,,这里有不好的东西吗\N{\rEng}Is there something bad here?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:38.39,0:32:41.01,Default,,0,0,0,,其实  博士  当某件事发生之后\N{\rEng}You know, Doc, when something happens...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:41.02,0:32:44.30,Default,,0,0,0,,它会在身后留下踪迹\N{\rEng}it can leave a trace of itself behind.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:45.52,0:32:46.72,Default,,0,0,0,,就比如说\N{\rEng}Say, like...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:47.24,0:32:49.71,Default,,0,0,0,,有人烤焦了吐司\N{\rEng}if someone burns toast.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:52.43,0:32:57.38,Default,,0,0,0,,也许某些事发生后会留下其他类型的踪迹\N{\rEng}Maybe things that happen leave other kind of traces behind.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:58.24,0:33:01.27,Default,,0,0,0,,不是人人都能注意得到的踪迹\N{\rEng}Not things that anyone can notice.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:01.80,0:33:06.60,Default,,0,0,0,,只有拥有闪灵能力的人才能看到的踪迹\N{\rEng}But things that people who shine can see.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:07.76,0:33:10.83,Default,,0,0,0,,就像他们能看见尚未发生的事情一样\N{\rEng}Just like they can see things that haven't happened yet...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:13.40,0:33:17.16,Default,,0,0,0,,有时他们也能看见很久以前发生的事\N{\rEng}sometimes they can see things that happened a long time ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:19.00,0:33:22.00,Default,,0,0,0,,我觉得就这家酒店\N{\rEng}I think a lot of things happened right here
Dialogue: 0,0:33:22.06,0:33:25.61,Default,,0,0,0,,多年来肯定发生过很多事\N{\rEng}in this particular hotel over the years.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:26.36,0:33:28.72,Default,,0,0,0,,并不全是好事\N{\rEng}And not all of them was good.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:32.05,0:33:34.42,Default,,0,0,0,,237号房是怎么回事\N{\rEng}What about room 237?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:38.09,0:33:39.87,Default,,0,0,0,,237号房\N{\rEng}Room 237?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:41.56,0:33:44.26,Default,,0,0,0,,你害怕237号房  不是吗\N{\rEng}You're scared of room 237, ain't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:46.37,0:33:48.32,Default,,0,0,0,,不  我没有\N{\rEng}No, I ain't.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:49.36,0:33:52.75,Default,,0,0,0,,哈洛兰先生  237号房里有什么\N{\rEng}Mr. Hallorann, what is in room 237?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:54.63,0:33:55.60,Default,,0,0,0,,什么都没有\N{\rEng}Nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:56.32,0:33:59.31,Default,,0,0,0,,237号房里什么都没有\N{\rEng}There ain't nothing in room 237.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:59.81,0:34:03.09,Default,,0,0,0,,但反正你也不需要进去做什么事\N{\rEng}But you ain't got no business going in there anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:03.32,0:34:05.36,Default,,0,0,0,,所以别进去\N{\rEng}So stay out.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:05.56,0:34:07.78,Default,,0,0,0,,你明白吗  别进去\N{\rEng}You understand? Stay out!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:10.14,0:34:13.08,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8\pos(192,152)}{\fn方正兰亭中黑_GBK\fs30\b0\bord0\shad0\3c&H2F2F2F&\c&HFFFFFF&}一个月后
Dialogue: 0,0:35:47.60,0:35:48.98,Default,,0,0,0,,早  亲爱的\N{\rEng}Good morning, hon.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:51.22,0:35:52.71,Default,,0,0,0,,你的早餐好了\N{\rEng}Your breakfast is ready.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:53.80,0:35:55.32,Default,,0,0,0,,几点了\N{\rEng}What time is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:55.69,0:35:57.25,Default,,0,0,0,,大概11点半\N{\rEng}It's about 11:30.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:57.84,0:36:00.80,Default,,0,0,0,,11点半  老天啊\N{\rEng}Eleven-thirty, Jesus.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:01.94,0:36:03.90,Default,,0,0,0,,我们熬夜熬得太晚了\N{\rEng}I guess we've been staying up too late.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:04.64,0:36:05.85,Default,,0,0,0,,我知道\N{\rEng}I know it.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:07.49,0:36:09.96,Default,,0,0,0,,我按你的喜好煎了蛋  只煎一面\N{\rEng}I made them just the way you like them, sunny-side up.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:10.98,0:36:11.99,Default,,0,0,0,,真棒\N{\rEng}Nice.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:14.45,0:36:16.07,Default,,0,0,0,,外面很漂亮\N{\rEng}It's really pretty outside.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:16.47,0:36:19.32,Default,,0,0,0,,你吃完早餐之后  带我出去散散步怎么样\N{\rEng}How about taking me for a walk after you finish your breakfast?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:20.32,0:36:24.34,Default,,0,0,0,,我应该先试着写点东西\N{\rEng}I suppose I ought to try to do some writing first.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:26.03,0:36:27.38,Default,,0,0,0,,有灵感了吗\N{\rEng}Any ideas yet?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:28.75,0:36:30.38,Default,,0,0,0,,思如泉涌\N{\rEng}Lots of ideas.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:30.67,0:36:31.98,Default,,0,0,0,,可惜都算不上好\N{\rEng}No good ones.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:32.66,0:36:34.81,Default,,0,0,0,,你会想到好点子的\N{\rEng}Well, something will come.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:35.49,0:36:39.28,Default,,0,0,0,,关键是你得适应每天都写作的习惯\N{\rEng}It's just a matter of settling into the habit of writing every day.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:40.13,0:36:42.39,Default,,0,0,0,,是啊  那就是关键\N{\rEng}Yep. That's all it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:44.88,0:36:46.84,Default,,0,0,0,,这里真的很好  对吧\N{\rEng}It's really nice up here, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:47.61,0:36:48.67,Default,,0,0,0,,我爱这里\N{\rEng}I love it.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:49.61,0:36:50.90,Default,,0,0,0,,真的很爱\N{\rEng}I really do.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:52.21,0:36:55.26,Default,,0,0,0,,我从来没这么开心自在过\N{\rEng}I've never been this happy or comfortable anywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:55.66,0:36:58.76,Default,,0,0,0,,你这么快就适应了这大房子  真好\N{\rEng}It's amazing how fast you get used to such a big place.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:59.21,0:37:02.22,Default,,0,0,0,,我跟你说  我们刚来的时候\N{\rEng}I tell you, when we first came up here,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:02.24,0:37:04.50,Default,,0,0,0,,我还觉得这里有点吓人\N{\rEng}I thought it was kind of scary.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:04.80,0:37:07.02,Default,,0,0,0,,我立马就爱上了这里\N{\rEng}I fell in love with it right away.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:08.08,0:37:10.72,Default,,0,0,0,,我过来面试的时候\N{\rEng}When I came up here for my interview,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:11.30,0:37:14.96,Default,,0,0,0,,就好像以前来过这里\N{\rEng}it was as though I'd been here before.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:15.30,0:37:18.15,Default,,0,0,0,,我们都有过似曾相识的感觉\N{\rEng}I mean, we all have moments of déjà vu,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:18.15,0:37:20.05,Default,,0,0,0,,但这也太离奇了\N{\rEng}but this was ridiculous.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:21.07,0:37:23.33,Default,,0,0,0,,就好像我知道\N{\rEng}It was almost as though I knew
Dialogue: 0,0:37:23.33,0:37:26.57,Default,,0,0,0,,每个角落会有什么一样\N{\rEng}what was going to be around every corner.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:00.12,0:38:03.29,Default,,0,0,0,,输的人要打扫全美国  怎么样\N{\rEng}The loser has to keep America clean. How's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:03.40,0:38:05.66,Default,,0,0,0,,-好啊  -你输定了\N{\rEng}- All right. - And you're going to lose.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:06.18,0:38:09.09,Default,,0,0,0,,我要抓到你了  你最好跑快点\N{\rEng}And I'm going to get you. You'd better run fast!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:14.27,0:38:15.37,Default,,0,0,0,,小心\N{\rEng}Look out!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:15.72,0:38:17.60,Default,,0,0,0,,我要追上来了  知道吗\N{\rEng}I'm coming in close. All right?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:17.73,0:38:19.84,Default,,0,0,0,,输的人要把美国打扫干净\N{\rEng}Loser has to keep America clean.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:19.59,0:38:22.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8\pos(193.5,54)}{\fn方正黑体_GBK\fs14\bord0\fad(150,0)\shad0\3c&H2F2F2F&\c&H787880&}眺望迷宫
Dialogue: 0,0:38:19.84,0:38:21.97,Default,,0,0,0,,-不要啊  -要把美国打扫干净\N{\rEng}- Oh, no! - Keep America clean.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:21.97,0:38:22.65,Default,,0,0,0,,好吧\N{\rEng}Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:23.24,0:38:24.22,Default,,0,0,0,,丹尼  你赢了\N{\rEng}Danny, you win.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:24.89,0:38:26.55,Default,,0,0,0,,剩下的路我们就走走吧\N{\rEng}Let's take the rest of this walking.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:27.38,0:38:29.43,Default,,0,0,0,,-好  -真累\N{\rEng}- Okay. - Whew.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:29.82,0:38:31.17,Default,,0,0,0,,手给我\N{\rEng}Give me your hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:33.75,0:38:35.25,Default,,0,0,0,,很漂亮对吧\N{\rEng}Isn't it beautiful?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:35.88,0:38:36.82,Default,,0,0,0,,是啊\N{\rEng}Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:53.28,0:38:54.74,Default,,0,0,0,,死路\N{\rEng}Dead end.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:51.79,0:39:53.37,Default,,0,0,0,,我们成功了\N{\rEng}Woo, we made it.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:54.07,0:39:56.25,Default,,0,0,0,,-很漂亮对吧  -是啊\N{\rEng}- Isn't it beautiful? - Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:17.12,0:40:18.75,Default,,0,0,0,,真漂亮\N{\rEng}It's so pretty.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:19.64,0:40:20.60,Default,,0,0,0,,是啊\N{\rEng}Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:23.77,0:40:26.26,Default,,0,0,0,,我没想到会有这么大  你呢\N{\rEng}I didn't think it was going to be this big. Did you?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:26.58,0:40:27.52,Default,,0,0,0,,没想到\N{\rEng}Nope.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:28.69,0:40:31.71,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8\pos(192,152)}{\fn方正兰亭中黑_GBK\fs30\b0\bord0\shad0\3c&H2F2F2F&\c&HFFFFFF&}星期二
Dialogue: 0,0:40:37.93,0:40:39.71,Default,,0,0,0,,卢瑟福德因为1968年的枪击案\N{\rEng}Rutherford was serving a life sentence...
Dialogue: 0,0:40:39.71,0:40:42.44,Default,,0,0,0,,被判处无期徒刑\N{\rEng}for his conviction in the 1968 shooting.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:42.44,0:40:45.00,Default,,0,0,0,,警方仍在乌雷附近的山中\N{\rEng}And the search continues in the mountains near Uray today
Dialogue: 0,0:40:45.00,0:40:46.63,Default,,0,0,0,,搜寻那位失踪的阿斯彭女子\N{\rEng}for that missing Aspen woman.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:46.64,0:40:50.13,Default,,0,0,0,,24岁的苏珊·罗伯森已失踪十天\N{\rEng}Twenty-four-year-old Susan Robertson has been missing 10 days.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:50.13,0:40:53.03,Default,,0,0,0,,她在和丈夫外出打猎时失踪\N{\rEng}She disappeared while on a hunting trip with her husband.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:53.05,0:40:54.30,Default,,0,0,0,,目前的天气很好\N{\rEng}They have good weather right now,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:54.30,0:40:56.09,Default,,0,0,0,,但如果预计的暴风雪明日到达\N{\rEng}but they may have to call off the search...
Dialogue: 0,0:40:56.09,0:40:58.77,Default,,0,0,0,,他们可能不得不叫停搜索\N{\rEng}if a predicted snowstorm moves in tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:58.77,0:41:00.59,Default,,0,0,0,,但是今天丹佛的天气这么好\N{\rEng}But it's so beautiful in Denver today,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:00.60,0:41:03.29,Default,,0,0,0,,很难想象马上就会有暴风雪\N{\rEng}it's hard to believe a snowstorm could be that close.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:03.30,0:41:05.73,Default,,0,0,0,,我知道  我也想出去沐浴阳光\N{\rEng}I know. I want to go outside and lie in the sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:05.73,0:41:09.83,Default,,0,0,0,,但是我们的北面和西面都在下雪  很冷\N{\rEng}Yet to our north, to our west, it is snowing and cold.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:09.83,0:41:13.93,Default,,0,0,0,,此刻  暴风雪正朝着科罗拉多州袭来\N{\rEng}And it's moving right here towards Colorado as we talk.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:13.93,0:41:15.27,Default,,0,0,0,,真是难以置信\N{\rEng}It's incredible.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:43.24,0:43:44.46,Default,,0,0,0,,你好  亲爱的\N{\rEng}Hi, hon.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:48.21,0:43:49.27,Default,,0,0,0,,怎么样了\N{\rEng}How's it going?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:52.29,0:43:53.25,Default,,0,0,0,,挺好的\N{\rEng}Fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:55.52,0:43:57.02,Default,,0,0,0,,今天写了很多吗\N{\rEng}Get a lot written today?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:59.36,0:44:00.38,Default,,0,0,0,,是的\N{\rEng}Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:02.94,0:44:06.40,Default,,0,0,0,,话说  天气预报说今晚会下雪\N{\rEng}Hey, the weather forecast said it's going to snow tonight.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:11.96,0:44:13.86,Default,,0,0,0,,那你要我怎样\N{\rEng}What do you want me to do about it?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:16.72,0:44:18.19,Default,,0,0,0,,别这样  亲爱的\N{\rEng}Come on, hon.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:18.87,0:44:20.29,Default,,0,0,0,,别这么暴躁\N{\rEng}Don't be so grouchy.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:21.38,0:44:22.56,Default,,0,0,0,,我没有\N{\rEng}I'm not...
Dialogue: 0,0:44:23.09,0:44:24.48,Default,,0,0,0,,暴躁\N{\rEng}being grouchy.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:24.48,0:44:26.66,Default,,0,0,0,,我就是想完成作品\N{\rEng}I just want to finish my work.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:30.73,0:44:32.81,Default,,0,0,0,,好的  我明白\N{\rEng}Okay. I understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:33.32,0:44:36.21,Default,,0,0,0,,我一会儿再给你带几个三明治过来\N{\rEng}I'll come back later on with a couple of sandwiches for you and...
Dialogue: 0,0:44:36.22,0:44:38.17,Default,,0,0,0,,可能你就会让我看一点了\N{\rEng}maybe you'll let me read something then.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:41.83,0:44:42.77,Default,,0,0,0,,温蒂\N{\rEng}Wendy,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:43.32,0:44:45.28,Default,,0,0,0,,我跟你解释一下\N{\rEng}let me explain something to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:46.64,0:44:48.94,Default,,0,0,0,,只要你进来  打扰我\N{\rEng}Whenever you come in here and interrupt me,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:48.94,0:44:50.81,Default,,0,0,0,,你就让我没法集中注意力\N{\rEng}you're breaking my concentration.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:50.81,0:44:52.18,Default,,0,0,0,,你在让我分心\N{\rEng}You're distracting me,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:52.18,0:44:55.78,Default,,0,0,0,,我要花很久才能回到之前的状态\N{\rEng}and it will then take me time to get back to where I was.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:56.09,0:44:57.13,Default,,0,0,0,,懂了吗\N{\rEng}Understand?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:59.12,0:45:00.04,Default,,0,0,0,,懂了\N{\rEng}Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:00.99,0:45:01.86,Default,,0,0,0,,很好\N{\rEng}Fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:03.24,0:45:05.12,Default,,0,0,0,,我们要定一条新规矩\N{\rEng}Now we're going to make a new rule.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:05.19,0:45:06.57,Default,,0,0,0,,只要我在这里\N{\rEng}Whenever I'm in here
Dialogue: 0,0:45:06.90,0:45:08.49,Default,,0,0,0,,你听见我在打字\N{\rEng}and you hear me typing,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:10.85,0:45:12.14,Default,,0,0,0,,或者你没听见我打字\N{\rEng}or whether you don't hear me typing,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:12.14,0:45:13.84,Default,,0,0,0,,或者不管你听见我在这里面做什么\N{\rEng}or whatever the fuck you hear me doing in here,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:13.84,0:45:16.43,Default,,0,0,0,,只要我在这里  就意味着我在工作\N{\rEng}when I'm in here, that means I am working,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:16.43,0:45:18.44,Default,,0,0,0,,也意味着不要进来\N{\rEng}that means don't come in.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:18.94,0:45:20.78,Default,,0,0,0,,这个你能做到吗\N{\rEng}Now, do you think you can handle that?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:23.85,0:45:24.84,Default,,0,0,0,,可以\N{\rEng}Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:25.79,0:45:26.75,Default,,0,0,0,,很好\N{\rEng}Fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:28.00,0:45:30.97,Default,,0,0,0,,不如你就从现在开始  马上滚远点\N{\rEng}Why don't you start right now and get the fuck out of here?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:35.01,0:45:35.91,Default,,0,0,0,,好吧\N{\rEng}Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:00.80,0:46:03.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8\pos(192,152)}{\fn方正兰亭中黑_GBK\fs30\b0\bord0\shad0\3c&H2F2F2F&\c&HFFFFFF&}星期四
Dialogue: 0,0:46:07.29,0:46:08.40,Default,,0,0,0,,你够了\N{\rEng}All right, you!
Dialogue: 0,0:46:10.04,0:46:11.67,Default,,0,0,0,,我知道你还有雪球\N{\rEng}I know you've got more.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:14.08,0:46:15.08,Default,,0,0,0,,没打中\N{\rEng}Missed!
Dialogue: 0,0:46:20.54,0:46:21.63,Default,,0,0,0,,没雪球了\N{\rEng}Don't have!
Dialogue: 0,0:46:21.63,0:46:23.13,Default,,0,0,0,,不公平了\N{\rEng}No fair anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:52.11,0:46:55.14,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8\pos(192,152)}{\fn方正兰亭中黑_GBK\fs30\b0\bord0\shad0\3c&H2F2F2F&\c&HFFFFFF&}星期六
Dialogue: 0,0:47:20.46,0:47:21.87,Default,,0,0,0,,别啊\N{\rEng}Oh, no.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:31.11,0:47:32.39,Default,,0,0,0,,我就知道\N{\rEng}I knew it.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:02.57,0:48:06.51,Default,,0,0,0,,KDK12号呼叫KDK1号\N{\rEng}This is KDK 12 calling KDK 1.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:08.58,0:48:12.46,Default,,0,0,0,,KDK12号呼叫KDK1号\N{\rEng}KDK 12 to KDK 1.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:12.58,0:48:15.39,Default,,0,0,0,,我是KDK1号  我们听到了  完毕\N{\rEng}This is KDK 1. We're receiving you. Over.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:16.01,0:48:18.98,Default,,0,0,0,,你好  我是眺望酒店的温蒂·托伦斯\N{\rEng}Hi, this is Wendy Torrance at the Overlook Hotel.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:19.69,0:48:22.33,Default,,0,0,0,,你好  你们在山上如何  完毕\N{\rEng}Hi, how are you folks getting on up there? Over.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:22.71,0:48:24.21,Default,,0,0,0,,我们挺好的\N{\rEng}We're just fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:24.29,0:48:26.96,Default,,0,0,0,,但是我们的电话似乎坏了\N{\rEng}But our telephones don't seem to be doing too well.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:27.00,0:48:30.46,Default,,0,0,0,,有没有可能是电话线断了  完毕\N{\rEng}Are the lines down, by any chance? Over.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:30.65,0:48:34.02,Default,,0,0,0,,没错  因为暴雪不少电话线都断了  完毕\N{\rEng}Yes, quite a few of them are down due to the storm. Over.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:34.70,0:48:37.94,Default,,0,0,0,,有可能尽快修好吗  完毕\N{\rEng}Any chance of them being repaired soon? Over.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:38.09,0:48:39.52,Default,,0,0,0,,我也不想这么说\N{\rEng}Well, I wouldn't like to say.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:39.53,0:48:42.61,Default,,0,0,0,,多数年份里  都要到春天才能修好  完毕\N{\rEng}Most winters they stay that way until spring. Over.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:43.46,0:48:46.75,Default,,0,0,0,,天啊  这暴风雪真的很强对吧  完毕\N{\rEng}Boy, this storm is really something, isn't it? Over.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:47.35,0:48:49.99,Default,,0,0,0,,没错  这是近几年来最强的一次\N{\rEng}Yes. It's one of the worst we've had for years.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:50.72,0:48:53.76,Default,,0,0,0,,有别的要帮忙的吗  托伦斯夫人  完毕\N{\rEng}Is there anything else we can do for you, Mrs. Torrance? Over.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:54.48,0:48:56.60,Default,,0,0,0,,我觉得没了  完毕\N{\rEng}I suppose not. Over.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:57.24,0:49:00.36,Default,,0,0,0,,如果你们在山上有麻烦  就跟我们联系\N{\rEng}If you folks have any problems up there, just give us a call.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:00.69,0:49:02.09,Default,,0,0,0,,另外  托伦斯夫人\N{\rEng}And, Mrs. Torrance?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:02.21,0:49:03.54,Default,,0,0,0,,我觉得你最好\N{\rEng}I think it might be a good idea
Dialogue: 0,0:49:03.54,0:49:07.09,Default,,0,0,0,,一直把无线电开着  完毕\N{\rEng}if you leave your radio on all the time now. Over.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:07.29,0:49:09.00,Default,,0,0,0,,好的  那我们就开着\N{\rEng}Okay. We'll do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:09.02,0:49:10.89,Default,,0,0,0,,跟你通话很愉快\N{\rEng}It was real nice talking to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:11.26,0:49:13.41,Default,,0,0,0,,再见  完毕  退出\N{\rEng}Bye. Over and out.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:48.85,0:49:50.72,Default,,0,0,0,,你好  丹尼\N{\rEng}Hello, Danny.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:56.27,0:49:58.32,Default,,0,0,0,,来和我们一起玩吧\N{\rEng}Come and play with us.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:03.59,0:50:05.88,Default,,0,0,0,,来和我们一起玩吧  丹尼\N{\rEng}Come and play with us, Danny.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:08.28,0:50:09.80,Default,,0,0,0,,永远\N{\rEng}For ever...
Dialogue: 0,0:50:11.87,0:50:13.42,Default,,0,0,0,,永远\N{\rEng}and ever...
Dialogue: 0,0:50:14.66,0:50:16.29,Default,,0,0,0,,永远\N{\rEng}and ever.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:48.12,0:50:49.51,Default,,0,0,0,,托尼\N{\rEng}Tony,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:50.60,0:50:52.38,Default,,0,0,0,,我害怕\N{\rEng}I'm scared.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:58.16,0:51:01.48,Default,,0,0,0,,记住哈洛兰先生说的话\N{\rEng}Remember what Mr. Hallorann said.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:03.37,0:51:07.00,Default,,0,0,0,,这就像书里的插画  丹尼\N{\rEng}It's just like pictures in a book, Danny.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:07.51,0:51:09.27,Default,,0,0,0,,这不是真的\N{\rEng}It isn't real.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:16.10,0:51:20.11,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8\pos(192,152)}{\fn方正兰亭中黑_GBK\fs30\b0\bord0\shad0\3c&H2F2F2F&\c&HFFFFFF&}星期一
Dialogue: 0,0:51:21.06,0:51:23.08,Default,,0,0,0,,我给你些钱吧\N{\rEng}Please let me give you some money.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:23.08,0:51:24.80,Default,,0,0,0,,我没想要钱\N{\rEng}I wouldn't think of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:25.31,0:51:27.02,Default,,0,0,0,,那我该如何报答你\N{\rEng}Well, how can I repay you?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:27.61,0:51:29.11,Default,,0,0,0,,没事的  真的\N{\rEng}It's okay. Really.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:30.09,0:51:32.13,Default,,0,0,0,,我去煮一点咖啡\N{\rEng}Well, I'm going to have some coffee.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:32.43,0:51:33.80,Default,,0,0,0,,你想喝吗\N{\rEng}Would you like some?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:35.71,0:51:36.71,Default,,0,0,0,,好啊\N{\rEng}Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:36.93,0:51:38.51,Default,,0,0,0,,太好了  坐下\N{\rEng}Great. Sit down.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:47.78,0:51:51.05,Default,,0,0,0,,好吃的甜甜圈  请自便\N{\rEng}Ooh, these marvellous doughnuts. Help yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:52.94,0:51:54.84,Default,,0,0,0,,-咖啡过几分钟就好  -妈妈\N{\rEng}- Coffee will be ready in a few minutes. - Mom?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:57.36,0:51:58.37,Default,,0,0,0,,怎么了\N{\rEng}Yeah?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:59.25,0:52:02.18,Default,,0,0,0,,我可以去我的房间拿消防车吗\N{\rEng}Can I go up to my room and get my fire-engine?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:03.97,0:52:06.45,Default,,0,0,0,,现在不行  爸爸在睡觉\N{\rEng}Not right now. Daddy's asleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:07.75,0:52:09.53,Default,,0,0,0,,我不会发出声音的\N{\rEng}I won't make any noise.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:11.32,0:52:12.82,Default,,0,0,0,,别闹  博士\N{\rEng}Come on, Doc.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:13.29,0:52:15.38,Default,,0,0,0,,他几个小时之前才去睡觉\N{\rEng}He only went to bed a few hours ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:15.38,0:52:16.93,Default,,0,0,0,,你不能等他起来再拿吗\N{\rEng}Can't you wait till later?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:17.29,0:52:20.04,Default,,0,0,0,,我不会发出声音的  我保证会踮着脚走\N{\rEng}I won't make a sound. I promise I'll tiptoe.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:22.29,0:52:24.62,Default,,0,0,0,,那好吧\N{\rEng}Well, all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:25.12,0:52:27.52,Default,,0,0,0,,不过千万别发出声音\N{\rEng}But really don't make a sound.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:27.77,0:52:28.88,Default,,0,0,0,,我不会的  妈妈\N{\rEng}I won't, Mom.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:30.14,0:52:31.83,Default,,0,0,0,,你拿到了就马上回来\N{\rEng}Make sure you come right back,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:31.83,0:52:33.60,Default,,0,0,0,,因为我很快要做午餐了\N{\rEng}because I'm going to make lunch soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:34.82,0:52:37.13,Default,,0,0,0,,-知道了吗  -知道了  妈妈\N{\rEng}- Okay? - Okay, Mom.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:26.84,0:53:29.74,Default,,0,0,0,,我可以去我的房间拿消防车吗\N{\rEng}Can I go to my room and get my fire-engine?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:33.70,0:53:35.74,Default,,0,0,0,,先到这里来一下\N{\rEng}Come here for a minute first.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:13.12,0:54:14.35,Default,,0,0,0,,你还好吗  博士\N{\rEng}How's it going, Doc?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:16.16,0:54:17.09,Default,,0,0,0,,挺好的\N{\rEng}Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:19.31,0:54:20.69,Default,,0,0,0,,玩得开心吗\N{\rEng}Having a good time?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:23.23,0:54:24.25,Default,,0,0,0,,开心  爸爸\N{\rEng}Yes, Dad.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:27.65,0:54:28.37,Default,,0,0,0,,那就好\N{\rEng}Good.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:31.15,0:54:32.74,Default,,0,0,0,,我希望你能开心\N{\rEng}I want you to have a good time.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:33.98,0:54:35.00,Default,,0,0,0,,我很开心  爸爸\N{\rEng}I am, Dad.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:41.99,0:54:42.69,Default,,0,0,0,,爸爸\N{\rEng}Dad?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:43.84,0:54:44.51,Default,,0,0,0,,怎么了\N{\rEng}Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:45.97,0:54:47.32,Default,,0,0,0,,你不舒服吗\N{\rEng}Do you feel bad?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:50.52,0:54:51.18,Default,,0,0,0,,没有\N{\rEng}No.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:53.77,0:54:55.49,Default,,0,0,0,,我就是有点累\N{\rEng}I'm just a little bit tired.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:57.60,0:54:59.57,Default,,0,0,0,,那你为什么不睡觉\N{\rEng}Then why don't you go to sleep?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:03.77,0:55:04.76,Default,,0,0,0,,我不能睡\N{\rEng}I can't.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:06.80,0:55:08.49,Default,,0,0,0,,我还有很多活要干\N{\rEng}I got too much to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:12.42,0:55:13.14,Default,,0,0,0,,爸爸\N{\rEng}Dad?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:15.55,0:55:16.19,Default,,0,0,0,,怎么了\N{\rEng}Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:18.22,0:55:20.02,Default,,0,0,0,,你喜欢这个酒店吗\N{\rEng}Do you like this hotel?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:24.05,0:55:24.77,Default,,0,0,0,,是啊\N{\rEng}Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:26.65,0:55:27.38,Default,,0,0,0,,我喜欢\N{\rEng}I do.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:29.04,0:55:29.90,Default,,0,0,0,,我很爱它\N{\rEng}I love it.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:32.50,0:55:33.26,Default,,0,0,0,,你不喜欢吗\N{\rEng}Don't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:36.24,0:55:37.31,Default,,0,0,0,,喜欢吧\N{\rEng}I guess so.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:40.38,0:55:40.99,Default,,0,0,0,,那就好\N{\rEng}Good.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:44.79,0:55:46.65,Default,,0,0,0,,我希望你喜欢这里\N{\rEng}I want you to like it here.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:51.16,0:55:54.26,Default,,0,0,0,,我希望我们可以永远待在这里\N{\rEng}I wish we could stay here forever...
Dialogue: 0,0:55:54.77,0:55:55.96,Default,,0,0,0,,永远\N{\rEng}and ever...
Dialogue: 0,0:55:57.05,0:55:57.92,Default,,0,0,0,,永远\N{\rEng}and ever.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:00.96,0:56:01.66,Default,,0,0,0,,爸爸\N{\rEng}Dad?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:03.93,0:56:04.62,Default,,0,0,0,,怎么了\N{\rEng}What?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:06.23,0:56:08.86,Default,,0,0,0,,你永远不会伤害我和妈妈  对吧\N{\rEng}You would never hurt Mommy or me, would you?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:14.96,0:56:15.94,Default,,0,0,0,,什么意思\N{\rEng}What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:21.45,0:56:23.55,Default,,0,0,0,,你妈妈跟你那么说过吗\N{\rEng}Did your mother ever say that to you?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:24.74,0:56:26.05,Default,,0,0,0,,说我会伤害你们吗\N{\rEng}That I would hurt you?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:27.21,0:56:28.19,Default,,0,0,0,,没有  爸爸\N{\rEng}No, Dad.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:30.86,0:56:31.83,Default,,0,0,0,,你确定吗\N{\rEng}You sure?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:32.91,0:56:33.92,Default,,0,0,0,,是的  爸爸\N{\rEng}Yes, Dad.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:39.39,0:56:40.85,Default,,0,0,0,,我爱你  丹尼\N{\rEng}I love you, Danny.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:42.47,0:56:47.46,Default,,0,0,0,,我爱你胜过全世界任何东西\N{\rEng}I love you more than anything else in the whole world,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:48.80,0:56:51.36,Default,,0,0,0,,我绝不会伤害你\N{\rEng}and I would never do anything to hurt you,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:52.05,0:56:52.75,Default,,0,0,0,,绝对不会\N{\rEng}never.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:54.17,0:56:55.77,Default,,0,0,0,,你知道的  对吧\N{\rEng}You know that, don't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:56.60,0:56:57.70,Default,,0,0,0,,是的  爸爸\N{\rEng}Yes, Dad.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:59.23,0:56:59.89,Default,,0,0,0,,很好\N{\rEng}Good.
